This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it deals with sentiment analysis and opinion mining, which are common tasks in NLP. It also involves graph representation learning, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with user behavior information. Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves a heterogeneous graph. Finally, Software Engineering (cs.SE) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not focus on software development, but rather on a novel solution for a specific problem in NLP.
